 #!Rimdep Image Depth #!N #!EC #!N #!N This option determines the 
maximum number of possible colors (or shades of color) that Data 
Explorer can use in creating an image. With greater numbers, gradations 
are smoother and edges are sharper. The image is "clearer." The 
choices are the number of bits available for specifying colors: 8 
(256 colors), 12 (4096) and 24 (more than 16 million). Data 
Explorer supports 8 bits. With the appropriate graphics card, it will 
process 12 and 24 bits. #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic 
